#. <section class="sutta" id="mn20"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn20:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 20"
msgstr "Middle Discourses 20"

# BB’s title is curious, given that there is nothing corresponding to “distracting”, and that saṇṭhana means “stopping, stilling”, not “removal”.
#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn20:0.2"
msgid "Vitakkasaṇṭhānasutta"
msgstr "How to Stop Thinking"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya1"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.119"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—​"
msgstr "So I have heard."

msgctxt "mn20:1.2"
msgid ""
"ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, "
"Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery."

msgctxt "mn20:1.3"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā bhikkhū āmantesi:"
msgstr "There the Buddha addressed the mendicants:"

msgctxt "mn20:1.4"
msgid "“bhikkhavo”ti."
msgstr "“Mendicants!”"

msgctxt "mn20:1.5"
msgid "“Bhadante”ti te bhikkhū bhagavato paccassosuṃ."
msgstr "“Venerable sir,” they replied."

msgctxt "mn20:1.6"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca:"
msgstr "The Buddha said this:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya2"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Adhicittamanuyuttena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā pañca nimittāni kālena kālaṃ "
"manasi kātabbāni."
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, a mendicant committed to the higher mind should focus on five "
"aspects of meditation from time to time."

msgctxt "mn20:2.2"
msgid "Katamāni pañca?"
msgstr "What five?"

#. <a class="nya" id="nya3"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:3.1"
msgid ""
"Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto "
"uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi "
"mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ "
"manasi kātabbaṃ kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Take a mendicant who is focusing on some aspect of meditation that gives "
"rise to bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion. "
"That mendicant should focus on some other aspect of meditation connected "
"with the skillful."

msgctxt "mn20:3.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ ye pāpakā "
"akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te "
"pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end."

#. VAR: hoti → ekodibhoti (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn20:3.3"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes "
"immersed in samādhi."

#. VAR: abhinivatteyya → abhinivajjeyya (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn20:3.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, dakkho palagaṇḍo vā palagaṇḍantevāsī vā sukhumāya "
"āṇiyā oḷārikaṃ āṇiṃ abhinihaneyya abhinīhareyya abhinivatteyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like an expert carpenter or their apprentice who’d knock out or extract "
"a large peg with a finer peg."

msgctxt "mn20:3.5"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ "
"manasikaroto uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi "
"dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tamhā nimittā "
"aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasi kātabbaṃ kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant … should focus on some other aspect of "
"meditation connected with the skillful …"

msgctxt "mn20:3.6"
msgid ""
"Tassa tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ ye pāpakā "
"akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te "
"pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn20:3.7"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati. (1)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya4"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.120"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:4.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto "
"kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi "
"dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ "
"ādīnavo upaparikkhitabbo:"
msgstr ""
"Now, suppose that mendicant is focusing on some other aspect of meditation "
"connected with the skillful, but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with "
"desire, hate, and delusion keep coming up. They should examine the drawbacks "
"of those thoughts:"

msgctxt "mn20:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘itipime vitakkā akusalā, itipime vitakkā sāvajjā, itipime vitakkā "
"dukkhavipākā’ti."
msgstr ""
"‘So these thoughts are unskillful, they’re blameworthy, and they result in "
"suffering.’"

msgctxt "mn20:4.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr "As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end."

msgctxt "mn20:4.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes "
"immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "mn20:4.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, itthī vā puriso vā daharo yuvā maṇḍanakajātiko "
"ahikuṇapena vā kukkurakuṇapena vā manussakuṇapena vā kaṇṭhe āsattena "
"aṭṭiyeyya harāyeyya jiguccheyya;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a woman or man who was young, youthful, and fond of "
"adornments. If the corpse of a snake or a dog or a human was hung around "
"their neck, they’d be horrified, repelled, and disgusted."

msgctxt "mn20:4.6"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tamhāpi nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ "
"manasikaroto kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, "
"bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ ādīnavo upaparikkhitabbo:"
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant … should examine the drawbacks of those "
"thoughts …"

msgctxt "mn20:4.7"
msgid ""
"‘itipime vitakkā akusalā, itipime vitakkā sāvajjā, itipime vitakkā "
"dukkhavipākā’ti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn20:4.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn20:4.9"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati. (2)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya5"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:5.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato "
"uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi "
"mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ "
"asatiamanasikāro āpajjitabbo."
msgstr ""
"Now, suppose that mendicant is examining the drawbacks of those thoughts, "
"but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion keep "
"coming up. They should try to ignore and forget about them."

msgctxt "mn20:5.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr "As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end."

msgctxt "mn20:5.3"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes "
"immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "mn20:5.4"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, cakkhumā puriso āpāthagatānaṃ rūpānaṃ adassanakāmo "
"assa;"
msgstr ""
"Suppose there was a person with good eyesight, and some undesirable sights "
"came into their range of vision."

msgctxt "mn20:5.5"
msgid "so nimīleyya vā aññena vā apalokeyya;"
msgstr "They’d just close their eyes or look away."

# MS text messes up the abbreviation here. PTS abbreviates more heavily.
msgctxt "mn20:5.6"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ "
"upaparikkhato uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi "
"dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi, te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant … should try to ignore and forget about those "
"thoughts …"

msgctxt "mn20:5.7"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati. (3)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya6"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:6.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato "
"uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi "
"mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ "
"vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikātabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"Now, suppose that mendicant is ignoring and forgetting about those thoughts, "
"but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and delusion keep "
"coming up. They should focus on stopping the formation of thoughts."

msgctxt "mn20:6.2"
msgid ""
"Tassa tesaṃ vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikaroto ye pāpakā "
"akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te "
"pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end."

msgctxt "mn20:6.3"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes "
"immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "mn20:6.4"
msgid "Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, puriso sīghaṃ gaccheyya."
msgstr "Suppose there was a person walking quickly."

msgctxt "mn20:6.5"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "mn20:6.6"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ sīghaṃ gacchāmi?"
msgstr "‘Why am I walking so quickly?"

msgctxt "mn20:6.7"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ saṇikaṃ gaccheyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I slow down?’"

msgctxt "mn20:6.8"
msgid "So saṇikaṃ gaccheyya."
msgstr "So they’d slow down."

msgctxt "mn20:6.9"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "mn20:6.10"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ saṇikaṃ gacchāmi?"
msgstr "‘Why am I walking slowly?"

msgctxt "mn20:6.11"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ tiṭṭheyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I stand still?’"

msgctxt "mn20:6.12"
msgid "So tiṭṭheyya."
msgstr "So they’d stand still."

msgctxt "mn20:6.13"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "mn20:6.14"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ ṭhito?"
msgstr "‘Why am I standing still?"

msgctxt "mn20:6.15"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ nisīdeyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I sit down?’"

msgctxt "mn20:6.16"
msgid "So nisīdeyya."
msgstr "So they’d sit down."

msgctxt "mn20:6.17"
msgid "Tassa evamassa:"
msgstr "They’d think:"

msgctxt "mn20:6.18"
msgid "‘kiṃ nu kho ahaṃ nisinno?"
msgstr "‘Why am I sitting?"

msgctxt "mn20:6.19"
msgid "Yannūnāhaṃ nipajjeyyan’ti."
msgstr "Why don’t I lie down?’"

msgctxt "mn20:6.20"
msgid "So nipajjeyya."
msgstr "So they’d lie down."

#. VAR: abhinivajjetvā → abhi­nissaj­jetvā (s1-3)
msgctxt "mn20:6.21"
msgid ""
"Evañhi so, bhikkhave, puriso oḷārikaṃ oḷārikaṃ iriyāpathaṃ abhinivajjetvā "
"sukhumaṃ sukhumaṃ iriyāpathaṃ kappeyya."
msgstr ""
"And so that person would reject successively coarser postures and adopt more "
"subtle ones."

msgctxt "mn20:6.22"
msgid ""
"Evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ "
"asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"In the same way, a mendicant … should focus on stopping the formation of "
"thoughts …"

msgctxt "mn20:6.23"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati. (4)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya7"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.121"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:7.1"
msgid ""
"Tassa ce, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ "
"manasikaroto uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi "
"dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi."
msgstr ""
"Now, suppose that mendicant is focusing on stopping the formation of "
"thoughts, but bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and "
"delusion keep coming up."

# Note that both abhinigganh-and abhinippil-occur in Ss2 as physical acts that men and women might perform on each other out of lust. Abhisantap-is not found there; derived from tapas, it is found only in descriptions of Jian-style self-mortification.
msgctxt "mn20:7.2"
msgid ""
"Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā "
"cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhitabbaṃ abhinippīḷetabbaṃ abhisantāpetabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"With teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of the mouth, they "
"should squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind."

msgctxt "mn20:7.3"
msgid ""
"Tassa dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato "
"abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi "
"dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end."

msgctxt "mn20:7.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes "
"immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "mn20:7.5"
msgid ""
"Seyyathāpi, bhikkhave, balavā puriso dubbalataraṃ purisaṃ sīse vā gale vā "
"khandhe vā gahetvā abhiniggaṇheyya abhinippīḷeyya abhisantāpeyya;"
msgstr ""
"It’s like a strong man who grabs a weaker man by the head or throat or "
"shoulder and squeezes, squashes, and tortures them."

msgctxt "mn20:7.6"
msgid ""
"evameva kho, bhikkhave, tassa ce bhikkhuno tesampi vitakkānaṃ "
"vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikaroto uppajjanteva pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi."
msgstr "In the same way, a mendicant …"

msgctxt "mn20:7.7"
msgid ""
"Tena, bhikkhave, bhikkhunā dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā "
"cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhitabbaṃ abhinippīḷetabbaṃ abhisantāpetabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"with teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of the mouth, should "
"squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind."

msgctxt "mn20:7.8"
msgid ""
"Tassa dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato "
"abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi "
"dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "As they do so, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end."

msgctxt "mn20:7.9"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati. (5)"
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes "
"immersed in samādhi."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="nya" id="nya8"></a>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi1.122"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc7"></a>
#. VAR: Yato kho → yato ca kho (s1-3, mr)
msgctxt "mn20:8.1"
msgid ""
"Yato kho, bhikkhave, bhikkhuno yaṃ nimittaṃ āgamma yaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto "
"uppajjanti pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi "
"mohūpasaṃhitāpi, tassa tamhā nimittā aññaṃ nimittaṃ manasikaroto "
"kusalūpasaṃhitaṃ ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi "
"mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"Now, take the mendicant who is focusing on some aspect of meditation that "
"gives rise to bad, unskillful thoughts connected with desire, hate, and "
"delusion. They focus on some other aspect of meditation connected with the "
"skillful …"

msgctxt "mn20:8.2"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn20:8.3"
msgid ""
"Tesampi vitakkānaṃ ādīnavaṃ upaparikkhato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr "They examine the drawbacks of those thoughts …"

msgctxt "mn20:8.4"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn20:8.5"
msgid ""
"Tesampi vitakkānaṃ asatiamanasikāraṃ āpajjato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā "
"chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ "
"gacchanti."
msgstr "They try to ignore and forget about those thoughts …"

msgctxt "mn20:8.6"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn20:8.7"
msgid ""
"Tesampi vitakkānaṃ vitakkasaṅkhārasaṇṭhānaṃ manasikaroto ye pāpakā akusalā "
"vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te "
"abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr "They focus on stopping the formation of thoughts …"

msgctxt "mn20:8.8"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mn20:8.9"
msgid ""
"Dantebhidantamādhāya jivhāya tāluṃ āhacca cetasā cittaṃ abhiniggaṇhato "
"abhinippīḷayato abhisantāpayato ye pāpakā akusalā vitakkā chandūpasaṃhitāpi "
"dosūpasaṃhitāpi mohūpasaṃhitāpi te pahīyanti te abbhatthaṃ gacchanti."
msgstr ""
"With teeth clenched and tongue pressed against the roof of the mouth, they "
"squeeze, squash, and torture mind with mind. When they succeed in each of "
"these things, those bad thoughts are given up and come to an end."

msgctxt "mn20:8.10"
msgid ""
"Tesaṃ pahānā ajjhattameva cittaṃ santiṭṭhati sannisīdati ekodi hoti "
"samādhiyati."
msgstr ""
"Their mind becomes stilled internally; it settles, unifies, and becomes "
"immersed in samādhi."

msgctxt "mn20:8.11"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, bhikkhu vasī vitakkapariyāyapathesu."
msgstr "This is called a mendicant who is a master of the ways of thought."

msgctxt "mn20:8.12"
msgid ""
"Yaṃ vitakkaṃ ākaṅkhissati taṃ vitakkaṃ vitakkessati, yaṃ vitakkaṃ "
"nākaṅkhissati na taṃ vitakkaṃ vitakkessati."
msgstr ""
"They’ll think what they want to think, and they won’t think what they don’t "
"want to think."

#. VAR: vivattayi → vāvattayi (bj, pts1)
msgctxt "mn20:8.13"
msgid ""
"Acchecchi taṇhaṃ, vivattayi saṃyojanaṃ, sammā mānābhisamayā antamakāsi "
"dukkhassā”ti."
msgstr ""
"They’ve cut off craving, untied the fetters, and by rightly comprehending "
"conceit have made an end of suffering.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc8"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:8.14"
msgid "Idamavoca bhagavā."
msgstr "That is what the Buddha said."

msgctxt "mn20:8.15"
msgid "Attamanā te bhikkhū bhagavato bhāsitaṃ abhinandunti."
msgstr "Satisfied, the mendicants were happy with what the Buddha said."

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "mn20:8.16"
msgid "Vitakkasaṇṭhānasuttaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "mn20:8.17"
msgid "Sīhanādavaggo niṭṭhito dutiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc9"></a>
msgctxt "mn20:8.18"
msgid "Cūḷasīhanādalomahaṃsavaro,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn20:8.19"
msgid "Mahācūḷadukkhakkhandhaanumānikasuttaṃ;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn20:8.20"
msgid "Khilapatthamadhupiṇḍikadvidhāvitakka,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "mn20:8.21"
msgid "Pañcanimittakathā puna vaggo."
msgstr ""
